  <Name>k__BackingField: 2 Timothy
  fancyName: 
  nickname: 2ti
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: d0ec49142d5c7c24fb05ee739840cab0, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Greeting'
      title: Greeting
      number: 1
      content: ' Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus through the will of God, according
        to the promise of life which is in Christ Jesus, '
      comments: []
    - name: "2: Timothy\u2019s Spiritual Heritage"
      title: "Timothy\u2019s Spiritual Heritage"
      number: 2
      content: 'to Timothy, my dear child. Grace, mercy, and peace from God the Father
        and Christ Jesus our Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I am thankful to God, whom I have served with a clear conscience
        as my ancestors did, when I remember you constantly in my prayers night and
        day, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'longing to see you as I remember your tears, so that I may be filled
        with joy, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'remembering the sincere faith in you, which lived first in your grandmother
        Lois and your mother Eunice, and I am convinced that is in you also, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'for which reason I remind you to rekindle the gift of God that is
        in you through the laying on of my hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: "7: Exhortation to Share Paul\u2019s Suffering"
      title: "Exhortation to Share Paul\u2019s Suffering"
      number: 7
      content: 'For God has not given us a spirit of cowardice, but of power and
        love and self-discipline. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Therefore, do not be ashamed of the testimony about our Lord, nor
        me his prisoner, but suffer along with me for the gospel, according to the
        power of God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'who saved us and called us with a holy calling, not according to
        our works but according to his own purpose and grace that was given to us
        in Christ Jesus before time began, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'but has now been disclosed by the appearing of our Savior Jesus Christ,
        who has abolished death and brought to light life and immortality through
        the gospel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'for which I was appointed a proclaimer and an apostle and a teacher, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'for which reason also I suffer these things. But I am not ashamed,
        because I know in whom I have believed, and I am convinced that he is able
        to guard what I have entrusted until that day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Hold fast to the pattern of sound words which you heard from me,
        in the faith and love that are in Christ Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Guard the good deposit through the Holy Spirit who lives in us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'You know this, that all those in Asia turned away from me, among
        whom are Phygelus and Hermogenes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'May the Lord grant mercy to the household of Onesiphorus, because
        he refreshed me many times, and was not ashamed of my imprisonment, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'but when he was in Rome, he diligently sought me and found me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'May the Lord grant him to find mercy from the Lord in that day! And
        how much he served me in Ephesus you know very well. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Exhortation to Be Strong in Grace'
      title: Exhortation to Be Strong in Grace
      number: 1
      content: ' You, therefore, my child, be strong in the grace that is in Christ
        Jesus, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and the things which you have heard from me in the presence of many
        witnesses, entrust these things to faithful people who will be competent
        to teach others also. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Suffer together with me as a good soldier of Christ Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'No one who serves as a soldier is entangled in the activities of
        everyday life, so that he may please the one who enlisted him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And also if anyone competes he is not crowned unless he competes
        according to the rules. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The farmer who works hard must be the first to receive a share of
        the crops. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: A Trustworthy Saying'
      title: A Trustworthy Saying
      number: 7
      content: 'Consider what I am saying, for the Lord will grant you understanding
        in all these things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Remember Jesus Christ, raised from the dead, a descendant of David
        according to my gospel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'in connection with which I suffer misfortune to the point of imprisonment
        as a criminal, but the word of God is not bound. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Because of this, I endure all things for the sake of the chosen,
        in order that they also may obtain salvation which is in Christ Jesus with
        eternal glory. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The saying is trustworthy: For if we died with him, we will also
        live with him; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'if we endure, we will also reign with him; if we deny him, he also
        will deny us; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: A Worker Approved to God and Not Ashamed'
      title: A Worker Approved to God and Not Ashamed
      number: 13
      content: "if we are unfaithful, he remains faithful\u2014he cannot deny himself.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Remind people of these things, solemnly urging them before the Lord
        not to dispute about words. This is in no way beneficial and leads to the
        ruin of the hearers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Make every effort to present yourself approved to God, a worker having
        no need to be ashamed, guiding the word of truth along a straight path. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But avoid pointless chatter, for it will progress to greater ungodliness, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'and their message will spread like gangrene, among whom are Hymenaeus
        and Philetus, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'who have deviated concerning the truth by saying the resurrection
        has already taken place, and they are upsetting the faith of some. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "However, the solid foundation of God stands firm, having this seal:
        \u201CThe Lord knows those who are his,\u201D and \u201CEveryone who names
        the name of the Lord must abstain from unrighteousness.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Now in a great house there are not only gold and silver vessels,
        but also wooden and earthenware ones, some of which are for honorable use,
        and some of which are for ordinary use. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Therefore, if someone cleanses himself from these things, he will
        be a vessel for honorable use, set apart, useful to the Master, prepared
        for every good work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But flee from youthful desires, and pursue righteousness, faith,
        love, and peace, in company with those who call upon the Lord from a pure
        heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But avoid foolish and uninformed controversies, because you know
        that they produce quarrels. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And the slave of the Lord must not quarrel, but be kind toward everyone,
        skillful in teaching, tolerant, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'correcting those who are opposed with gentleness, seeing whether
        perhaps God may grant them repentance to a knowledge of the truth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'and they will come to their senses again and escape from the trap
        of the devil, being held captive by him to do his will. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Difficult Times Ahead in the Last Days'
      title: Difficult Times Ahead in the Last Days
      number: 1
      content: ' But know this, that in the last days difficult times will come, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'for people will be lovers of themselves, lovers of money, boasters,
        arrogant, slanderers, disobedient to parents, ungrateful, unholy, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'hardhearted, irreconcilable, slanderous, without self-control, savage,
        with no interest for what is good, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'traitors, reckless, conceited, loving pleasure rather than loving
        God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'maintaining a form of godliness, but denying its power. Avoid these
        people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For from these are those who slip into houses and captivate foolish
        women loaded down with sins, led by various kinds of desires, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'always learning and never able to come to a knowledge of the truth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And just as Jannes and Jambres opposed Moses, so also these oppose
        the truth, people corrupted in mind, disqualified concerning the faith. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: The Value of the Scriptures'
      title: The Value of the Scriptures
      number: 9
      content: 'But they will not progress to a greater extent, for their folly will
        be quite evident to everyone, as also the folly of those two was. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But you have faithfully followed my teaching, way of life, purpose,
        faith, patience, love, endurance, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'persecutions, and sufferings that happened to me in Antioch, in Iconium,
        and in Lystra, what sort of persecutions I endured, and the Lord delivered
        me from all of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And indeed, all those who want to live in a godly manner in Christ
        Jesus will be persecuted. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But evil people and imposters will progress to the worse, deceiving
        and being deceived. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But you continue in the things which you have learned and are convinced
        of, because you know from whom you learned them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and that from childhood you have known the holy writings that are
        able to make you wise for salvation through faith in Christ Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'All scripture is inspired by God and profitable for teaching, for
        reproof, for correction, for training in righteousness, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'in order that the person of God may be competent, equipped for every
        good work. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Paul\u2019s Charge to Timothy"
      title: "Paul\u2019s Charge to Timothy"
      number: 1
      content: ' I solemnly charge you before God and Christ Jesus, who is going
        to judge the living and the dead, and by his appearing and his kingdom, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'preach the word, be ready in season and out of season, reprove, rebuke,
        exhort, with all patience and instruction. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For there will be a time when they will not put up with sound teaching,
        but in accordance with their own desires, they will accumulate for themselves
        teachers, because they have an insatiable curiosity, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and they will turn away from the hearing of the truth, but will turn
        to myths. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But you, be self-controlled in all things, bear hardship patiently,
        do the work of an evangelist, fulfill your ministry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For I am already being poured out as a drink offering, and the time
        of my departure is imminent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I have fought the good fight, I have completed the race, I have kept
        the faith. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Final Instructions to Timothy'
      title: Final Instructions to Timothy
      number: 8
      content: 'Finally, the crown of righteousness is reserved for me, that the
        Lord, the righteous Judge, will award to me on that day, and not only to
        me, but also to all who have loved his appearing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Make haste to come to me quickly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For Demas deserted me, because he loved the present age, and went
        to Thessalonica. Crescens went to Galatia; Titus went to Dalmatia. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Luke alone is with me. Take along Mark and bring him with you, because
        he is useful to me for ministry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But I have sent Tychicus to Ephesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When you come, bring the cloak that I left behind in Troas with Carpus,
        and the scrolls, especially the parchments. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Alexander the metalworker did me much harm; may the Lord pay back
        to him according to his deeds, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'against whom you also be on guard, because he vehemently opposed
        our words. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'At my first defense, no one came to my aid, but they all deserted
        me; may it not be counted against them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But the Lord helped me and strengthened me, so that through me the
        proclamation might be fulfilled and all the Gentiles might hear, and he rescued
        me from the lion\u2019s mouth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Final Greetings and Benediction'
      title: Final Greetings and Benediction
      number: 18
      content: 'The Lord will rescue me from every evil deed, and will save me for
        his heavenly kingdom, to whom be the glory forever and ever. Amen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Greet Prisca and Aquila and the household of Onesiphorus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Erastus remained in Corinth, but Trophimus I left behind in Miletus
        because he was sick. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Make haste to come before winter. Eubulus and Pudens and Linus and
        Claudia and all the brothers greet you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The Lord be with your spirit. Grace be with you. '
      comments: []
